CAPE TOWN - Four people have died in an informal dwelling fire in Thembalethu, in George, on Monday. Two women, a man and a two-year-old toddler were discovered on the scene all burned beyond recognition. Thembalethu police have opened an inquest docket. The police's Christopher Spies said: “Emergency personnel responded and discovered the remains of four occupants on scene.” Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.